                            <comment id="14428643" author="bentmann" created="Sat, 23 Oct 2010 11:47:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed in &lt;a href=&quot;http://svn.apache.org/viewvc?view=revision&amp;amp;revision=1026646&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;r1026646&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14428885" author="jglick" created="Tue, 1 May 2012 17:03:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Probably it should mention &lt;tt&gt;-DskipTests&lt;/tt&gt; interpreted by Surefire, which is generally preferable: at least checks that tests compile, which does not take much time and can be expected to be reliable on all platforms, while not actually running them which might take a long time and be flaky.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
